                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d404">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/4984</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MEV1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-29T12:00:00-03:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1917, noon</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 6.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Foreign Relations Committee of Brazilian Chamber has recommended that Congress
                    authorize the Executive power to utilize German merchant vessels anchored in
                    Brazilian ports; also to take measures to defend Brazilian foreign commerce,
                    arranging the matter with friendly nations so as to assure freedom of
                    importation and exportation, revoking for this purpose present neutrality
                    decrees when such action may be expedient.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MEV1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
